awkwardly. We mariners, he would say, are
more accustomed to the boarding-pike than the
card-table
,
and he quite envied his companion's more
adroit and graceful motions. He was even known,
at times, to drop a card on the floor, so very
awkward
was he, and so bungling, and at times those
